{
  "openapi": "3.0.3",
  "info": {
    "title": "Poke Query API",
    "version": "1.0.0",
    "description": "A REST API for sharing and discovering Pokémon GO search queries.\n\n**Repository:** [github.com/jameshschuler/poke-query](https://github.com/jameshschuler/poke-query)\n\n## What This API Does\n\nTrainers can create, save, share, fork, favorite, and discover reusable in-game search strings (e.g. `cp2500-&!shadow`) with the community.\n\n## Getting Started\n\n### 1. Run the backend locally\n\n```bash\ncd backend\nnpm install\nnpm run db:migrate\nnpm run dev\n```\n\nThe server starts at **http://localhost:3000**.\n\n### 2. Authenticate\n\n1. `POST /auth/login` with your email — triggers an OTP email.\n2. `POST /auth/verify` with `email` + `token` (or `token_hash` from the magic link).\n3. The response sets an `sb-access-token` HttpOnly cookie. All protected endpoints require this cookie.\n\n### 3. Call a protected endpoint\n\n```bash\ncurl -X POST \"http://localhost:3000/api/v1/queries\" \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -H \"Cookie: sb-access-token=YOUR_TOKEN\" \\\n  -d '{\"title\":\"Great League IV\",\"query\":\"4*&cp-1500\",\"isPublic\":false}'\n```\n\n## Authentication Model\n\nThis API uses **cookie-based auth** via Supabase.\n\n| Detail | Value |\n|---|---|\n| Cookie name | `sb-access-token` |\n| Lifetime | 1 hour (access), 7 days (refresh) |\n| Protected routes | Marked with the 🔒 lock icon below |\n"
  },
  "components": {
    "securitySchemes": {
      "cookieAuth": {
        "type": "apiKey",
        "in": "cookie",
        "name": "sb-access-token",
        "description": "Supabase access token cookie"
      }
    },
    "schemas": {}
  },
  "paths": {
    "/auth/login": {
      "post": {
        "requestBody": {
          "required": true,
          "content": {
            "application/json": {
              "schema": {
                "type": "object",
                "required": [
                  "email"
                ],
                "properties": {
                  "email": {
                    "format": "email",
                    "type": "string"
                  }
                }
              }
            }
          }
        },
        "responses": {
          "200": {
            "description": "Default Response",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "type": "object",
                  "required": [
                    "message"
                  ],
                  "properties": {
